Structure of an IP Address (Short)

An IP (Internet Protocol) address is a unique numerical identifier assigned to every device connected to a network. It helps identify and locate devices for communication.

IP Structure:
- Length: 32 bits (4 bytes)
- Format: Four decimal numbers (octets) separated by dots.
- Example: 192.168.1.10
- Each octet ranges from 0 to 255.


Network ID: Identifies the network.
Host ID: Identifies the specific device on that network.
